{
  "stem": "1753.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 105.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And on the way home-- that was mid-morning-- we heard the airplanes, and the bombs fell all around us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So that was the day the war began, World War II.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And two days later, the Germans entered into Poznan, without a shot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the whole war was over three weeks later, except Warsaw was the only city that held out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that was the end.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then, the occupation began.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But a month later, the-- an order came from the German authorities, because Poznan was part of Pomerania, which was the corridor, which was reclaimed by the Germans to be annexed to the Deutszche Reich.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the governor was Hans Frank.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He gave an order, all Pomerania must be judenfrei.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they picked us up one morning to put us on trucks, and pushed us to Kalisz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there, they put us in-- in-- in a-- in-- in-- in-- in the basement of-- of-- of the City Hall.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were stuck there for three days with no food, and nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then they allowed us to leave, provided that we leave the city as quickly as possible.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Somehow, we organized some horse and wagons from the Polish population and traveled from there to Lodz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there are many, many cities.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There's Opatowek, and there's Praszka, and there's Sieradz, Zdunska Wola, Pabianice, and finally Lodz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When we came to Sieradz-- no, when we came to-- to Zdunska Wola, which was a-- that day was one-- exactly one year after Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I guess the Nazis wanted to celebrate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They rounded up-- there was a large Jewish population, that shtetled there in-- in-- in Zdunska Wola.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they rounded up everybody, maybe about 3,000 Jews, men.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we just happened to be there at the same time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were with some Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
